	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually, many people *don't* know the things you mentioned.  That's why they asked.
<br />
<br />In addition to reading through the technical docs on this site and the wiki, I'd recommend heading over to nintendoage.com, registering for the forums, and checking out the 'Nerdy Nights' tutorial in the 'Brewery' section of the forums.  It starts from the basics and gets you up to speed with CPU architecture, sprite and nametable basics, 6502 basics, etc.  It's gives you enough flavor to decide whether you'll want to continue or not.
<br />
<br />It seems most people sputter out after realizing how tough it is to program for the NES.  I've been reading off and on for over a year now and I still feel like a beginner.  Everyone learns at different speeds, so stick with it and you'll do fine.  You just have to really love the NES to get past the learning curve.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


